<!--
  ZA.Authorization v2.0.0 — intentional API breaks as part of the major version bump.

  Five breakages are suppressed, each across three TFMs (net8.0, net9.0, net10.0):
  - Two type removals: the v1 [AuthorizationPolicy] and [Authorize] attributes,
    renamed to [Policy] and [RequirePolicy] respectively. The rename eliminates
    the name collision with Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization.AuthorizeAttribute
    and provides a clean grammatical pair (declare-side / require-side).
  - Three method removals: the four-method IAuthorizationPolicy contract collapses
    to a single async EvaluateAsync (the surviving method). Sync-only policies
    wrap their result in new ValueTask<...>(result) — allocation-free on the stack.

  Each entry sets IsBaselineSuppression=true because the api-compat workflow
  compares the newly built nupkg against the latest released baseline (1.2.x).

  See docs/plans/2026-05-19-policy-registry-generator-design.md for the design
  decisions that led to these breaks.
-->
